      "parameters": {
        "content": "7. Message a Model (Sentiment Analysis)\nThis node sends the customer’s reply message to a Gemini model specifically for sentiment analysis. The prompt strictly instructs the model to classify sentiment as positive, neutral, or negative, return confidence between 0 and 1, and provide a short emotional explanation in JSON format only.\n\n8. Edit Fields2 (Sentiment Parsing)\nThis node parses the AI sentiment output JSON. It extracts three fields: Sentiment, Confidence, and Explanation. These values are converted into structured fields for logging and reporting.\n\n9. Conversation Information\nThis node logs the sentiment analysis result into a Google Sheets tab called “Customer Satisfaction”. It stores sentiment, confidence score, and explanation for tracking customer mood over time.",
